article.description: Tyron Criswell scored 26 points off the bench as Nevada beat Division II Fresno Pacific 119-70 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Nevada beats Div. II Fresno Pacific 119-70
article.linkText: Nevada beats Div. II Fresno Pacific 119-70
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- Tyron Criswell scored 26 points off the bench as Nevada beat Division II Fresno Pacific 119-70 on Wednesday night. Criswell finished with 9-of-10 shooting from the field and 8-of-8 from the line for the Wolf Pack (6-3). Cameron Oliver and Eric Cooper Jr. had 16 points apiece, Marqueze Coleman added 15 and Lindsey drew had 12. The Wolf Pack climbed to a 15-5 lead midway through the first period on their way to a 46-29 advantage at the break. They had a 97-44 lead with 7:33 left in the game and cruised to the win. Nevada averaged 59.7 percent shooting from the field, 76.5 percent from the line and hit 13 of 24 (54.2 percent) from beyond the arc. It also had a 60-24 rebounding edge over Fresno Pacific. Spencer Krannitz led the Sunbirds with 17 points, three assists and three steals.
